{
  "texts": [
    "Although all these approaches improve performance over a range of IR applications, they fail to consistently work well when trained on small-scale data.",
    "Pretrained Language ModelsCreating a better language model is crucial to NLP.",
    "In the broad sense, a pretrained language model refers to a language model trained on large-scale data, including distributed static representation-based models (word2vec [122] and GloVe [51]) and dynamic contextualized models (CoVe [19] and ELMo [73]).",
    "Following the new wave of deep transformer-focused pretrained models [10], such as the generative pretrained transformer (GPT) [10] developed by OpenAI, a new understanding of the pretrained language model, known as BERT [44], emerged in the NLP community in 2018.",
    "Compared with previous models [17,18,90,150], pretrained models based on deep transformer encoders have the advantage of being able to process input text sequences in parallel."
  ]
}